<subSubSection id="D64DC74CEF934E230C830EC17974394B" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="E26F9DA7FFE4C34557A9CE2FB1C39F35" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B3A6402E6CF43A7249A5D4FFF4DB1593" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults are active throughout spring and summer, ranging in total length 7-10 mm and 1.5-3 mm in maximum width. Like the other species of this genus, 
<taxonomicName id="3FA281B7F2D9232491C577F827CFF903" genus="A." lsidName="A. l. subsp. longicollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="subSpecies" species="l." subSpecies="longicollis">
<emphasis id="1100BFBA623B61A8E1A972417765146F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">A. l. longicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is nocturnal and readily attracted to artificial lights. There is no published information on its larval host plant(s).
</paragraph>
